reviews.review_text: - This very nice Matrix makes me reassess this show. It's actually pretty excellent, and shows how much of a difference the thorough treatment of a recording can make. The band are on top form instrumentally, though not on vocals, and the jams are inspired, varied, and dynamic

Sweet Magnolia Daydream An extremely tight Sugar Magnolia
Break out the time machine mosh pit.
Epic Worth the purchase price for the Dark Star and China>Rider alone. Like all '71 shows, slightly uneven performance, but I recommend giving this one a full play.
